### Segment Mode (Database-based)

Database table:

```mysql
CREATE TABLE `sys_id_sequence`
(
    `biz_key`      varchar(100) NOT NULL COMMENT 'Business dimension unique key',
    `max_id`       bigint       NOT NULL DEFAULT '0' COMMENT 'Current maximum allocated ID',
    `step`         int          NOT NULL DEFAULT '1000' COMMENT 'Step size',
    `version`      int          NOT NULL DEFAULT '0' COMMENT 'Version (optimistic lock)',
    `reset_policy` varchar(20)           DEFAULT 'NONE' COMMENT 'Reset policy: NONE/DAILY/HOURLY',
    `seq_length`   int                   DEFAULT '8' COMMENT 'Sequence length (left-padded with zeros)',
    `prefix`       varchar(50)           DEFAULT NULL COMMENT 'Prefix',
    PRIMARY KEY (`biz_key`)
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_0900_ai_ci COMMENT='Distributed ID sequence configuration table';
```

Each time, a range of IDs is fetched from the database, then auto-incremented in memory. IDs are consecutive.

```java
public class Segment {
        private final long start;
        private final long end;
        private final AtomicLong cursor;
        private volatile Segment next;

        public Segment(long start, long end) {
            this.start = start;
            this.end = end;
            this.cursor = new AtomicLong(start - 1);
        }

        /**
         * Get next ID
         */
        public long next() {
            long value = cursor.incrementAndGet();

            if (value <= end) {
                return value;
            }

            // Current segment exhausted, switch to next segment
            if (next != null) {
                return next.next();
            }

            throw new IllegalStateException("ID segment exhausted, and no prefetched next segment");
        }

        /**
         * Remaining available count
         */
        public long remaining() {
            long current = cursor.get();
            return Math.max(0, end - current);
        }

        /**
         * Set next segment
         */
        public void setNext(Segment next) {
            this.next = next;
        }
    }
```

### Prefetch Mechanism

```java
// When remaining count is below threshold, asynchronously prefetch next segment
if (segment.remaining() <= PREFETCH_THRESHOLD) {
    tryPrefetch(bizKey);
}
```

